acceptOwnership().details: Accept the ownership transfer. This is to make sure that the contract is transferred to a working address Can only be called by the newly transfered owner.

burn(uint256).details: Burns a bee token. Only the contract owner can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to burn.

getBeeLevel(uint256).details: Retrieves the bee characteristics for a given token ID. We have the equation to caculate XP per level: XP = (d x n x (n - 1))/2 with d is differenceBetweenLevels and n is bee level Transform the equation to: n^2 - n - 2XP/d = 0 (Bring the equation to the form ax^2 + bx + c = 0) Quadratic formula: x = (-b ± sqrt(b^2 - 4ac)) / 2a From the base equation, we have: n = (sqrt(8 * XP/d + 1) + 1)/2 using quadratic formula

getBeeTraits(uint256).details: Retrieves the bee characteristics for a given token ID.

getForagingNumQuestsForLevel(uint256).details: Retrieves the number of foraging quests for a given bee level. Caculation equation: Qfn = baseNumberOfForagingQuest + (n-1) x 2

getRaidNumQuestsForLevel(uint256).details: Retrieves the number of raid quests for a given bee level. Caculation equation: Qrn = baseNumberOfRaidQuest + n

getRaidSuccessNumQuestsForLevel(uint256).details: Retrieves the number of raid success quests for a given bee level. Caculation equation: Qrsn = baseNumberOfRaidSuccessQuest + (n-1) / 2

returns._0: The number of raid success quests.

getUpgradeNumQuestsForLevel(uint256).details: Retrieves the number of upgrade quests for a given bee level. Caculation equation: Qun = baseNumberOfUpgradeQuest + n

minFee().details: The amount fee that will be lost when transferring.

mintTo(address,uint256).details: Mints a new bee token and assigns it to the specified address. Only the contract owner can call this function. Reverts if the total supply exceeds the maximum supply.

params._beeType: The type of bee to mint, either 0 for worker or 1 for queen.
params.to: The address to mint the token to.

returns._0: The ID of the newly minted token.

modifyBeeTraits(uint256,uint256,(uint256.details: Modifies the traits of a bee token. Only the Hive contract can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to modify.

pause().details: Pauses the contract. Only the contract owner can call this function.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

refreshBeeEnergy(uint256).details: Refreshes the energy of a bee token.  Energy is refreshed each interval. Different bee types have different energy refresh rates.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to refresh.

refreshBeeHealth(uint256).details: Refreshes the health of a bee token.  Health is refreshed each interval. Different bee types have different health refresh rates.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to refresh.

setMintFee(uint256).details: Sets the mint fee for the contract. Only the contract owner can call this function.

params._mintFee: The new mint fee to set.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Retrieves the token URI for a given token ID.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Unpauses the contract. Only the contract owner can call this function.

updateForagingQuestCount(uint256,uint256.details: Updates the foraging quests progress for a bee. Only the Hive contract can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to update.

updateRaidQuestCount(uint256,uint256).details: Updates the raid quests progress for a bee. Only the Hive contract can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to update.

updateRaidSuccessQuestCount(uint256,uint.details: Updates the raid success quests progress for a bee. Only the Hive contract can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to update.

updateUpgradeQuestCount(uint256,uint256).details: Updates the upgrade quests progress for a bee. Only the Hive contract can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to update.

withdrawPayments(address).details: Withdraws the contract's balance to the specified address. Only the contract owner can call this function.

params.payee: The address to withdraw the balance to.
